32:41.320 --> 32:43.880
♪ L'étendard sanglant est levé

32:43.960 --> 32:48.920
♪ Entendez-vous dans les campagnes

32:53.760 --> 32:58.680
4-1 Liddell! What are you asking?

32:58.760 --> 33:00.840
£25, Liddell to win.

33:13.760 --> 33:15.880
Mr Mussabini, I believe.

33:15.960 --> 33:19.160
My name's Keddie. Colonel John Keddie.

33:19.240 --> 33:21.600
- I'm...
- President of the Scottish Three A's.

33:21.720 --> 33:24.480
I know, and I'm glad to know you, sir.

33:24.560 --> 33:27.360
- <i>Monsieur Sam! Bonjour.</i>
<i>- Bonjour.</i>

33:27.480 --> 33:29.120
- How's the leg?
- OK.

33:29.200 --> 33:30.880
Nasty fall you took.

33:31.000 --> 33:33.080
<i>Enchanté. Good luck.</i>

33:33.200 --> 33:35.360
You're very welcome here, of course.

33:35.480 --> 33:38.560
But we do have a strict amateur code.

33:39.400 --> 33:41.480
Colonel, don't worry your head.

33:41.560 --> 33:43.480
I'm here spectating, that's all.

33:43.560 --> 33:45.920
Good. I felt sure you would understand.

33:47.040 --> 33:49.160
Well, to battle!

33:49.240 --> 33:51.320
I hope you enjoy the games.

33:52.200 --> 33:54.280
Games? You must be joking.

33:54.360 --> 33:56.840
I've seen better-organised riots.

33:56.920 --> 33:59.880
Come on, Scotland!

34:00.000 --> 34:02.080
<i>Vive la France!</i>

34:11.040 --> 34:13.120
Gentlemen, get to your marks.

34:19.719 --> 34:21.280
Get set.

34:33.080 --> 34:35.159
Get up, lad. Get up.

34:40.159 --> 34:42.320
<i>Yeah.</i>

34:46.400 --> 34:48.360
He'll never do it.

34:48.440 --> 34:50.880
Don't you believe it. His head's not back yet.

35:00.680 --> 35:02.800
Come on, Eric!

35:36.640 --> 35:38.720
Get back! Give him air!

35:41.120 --> 35:43.600
Well done, Eric, son. Well done.

35:43.680 --> 35:46.760
He'll be right in a jiffy.
I'll go away and get his clothes.

35:52.160 --> 35:55.720
You take good care
of this lad o' yours, Mr McGrath.

35:55.800 --> 35:59.840
Because if you drop him,
you'll never find another one like this.

35:59.920 --> 36:03.080
It's not the prettiest quarter
I've ever seen, Mr Liddell.

36:03.160 --> 36:05.240
But certainly the bravest.

36:05.320 --> 36:07.440
Get him up. Come on, gently.

36:12.920 --> 36:15.000
Keep your arm around.

36:36.480 --> 36:38.560
Mr Mussabini.

36:40.680 --> 36:42.800
Mr Abrahams, is it?

36:43.480 --> 36:46.000
So you've travelled 300 mile just to see me?

36:46.080 --> 36:47.760
You and Liddell.

36:47.840 --> 36:49.920
I'd heard you were both the best.

36:50.000 --> 36:52.080
And what do you think now?

36:52.160 --> 36:54.240
Eric Liddell?

36:54.320 --> 36:58.000
I've never seen such drive,
such commitment in a runner.

36:58.600 --> 37:00.680
He runs like a wild animal.

37:00.760 --> 37:02.560
He unnerves me.

37:02.640 --> 37:04.440
So he should.

37:04.520 --> 37:07.120
He frightens the living daylights out of me.

37:07.240 --> 37:09.960
I want you to help me take him on.

37:12.600 --> 37:14.760
Tell me, Mr Abrahams. Are you married?

37:14.840 --> 37:16.920
No. Why?

37:17.040 --> 37:18.480
Well...

37:18.560 --> 37:21.360
when the right girl comes along...

37:21.440 --> 37:24.720
how will you feel if she pops the question?

37:27.400 --> 37:29.480
You see, Mr Abrahams...

37:29.560 --> 37:31.520
like the bridegroom...

37:31.600 --> 37:34.120
it's the coach that should do the asking.

37:35.280 --> 37:37.320
Mr Mussabini...

37:37.400 --> 37:39.440
I can run fast.

37:39.560 --> 37:42.400
With your help, I think I can run even faster.

37:42.520 --> 37:44.840
Perhaps faster than any man ever ran.

37:45.600 --> 37:47.680
I want that Olympic medal.

37:48.520 --> 37:50.600
Now, I can see it there.

37:50.680 --> 37:52.880
It's waiting for me.

37:52.960 --> 37:55.040
But I can't get it on my own.

38:01.560 --> 38:04.200
Well, we've an old saying in my game, son.

38:05.160 --> 38:07.360
You can't put in what God's left out.

38:08.240 --> 38:10.200
Now, you leave it to me.

38:10.280 --> 38:13.640
I'll watch you. I'll observe.
And if I think I can help...

38:14.880 --> 38:17.520
if I can see the big prize hanging there...

38:17.600 --> 38:20.120
believe me, I won't waste any time.

38:20.200 --> 38:22.560
When we meet again...

38:22.640 --> 38:24.760
I'll be the one that does the begging.

38:24.840 --> 38:26.800
So you will watch me?

38:26.880 --> 38:28.960
Son, if you're good enough...

38:30.480 --> 38:33.320
I'll take you apart piece by bloody piece.

38:34.000 --> 38:36.080
Thank you.

